
# install traceroute 
traceroute google.com
tracepath google.com 
# ss command is used to check network sockets 

 $ ss -at (shows all tcp sockets)
 $ ss -au (show all udp sockets) 

# If I want to see port number 
  
  $ ss -aun (udp port numbers)
  $ ss -atn (tcp port numbers)

# To check if my device is sending and recieving packets 

 $ ip -s link show eth0

RX-recieving 
TX-transmiting 


